26
00:02:49,150 --> 00:02:50,620
Just try it, come on.

27
00:02:53,370 --> 00:02:53,980
Is it good?

28
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:12,590
[Qiu Hua]

29
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:15,840
I need to take a call.

30
00:03:23,150 --> 00:03:23,960
Hello, Qiu Hua.

31
00:03:24,390 --> 00:03:25,880
Quanquan, where are you?

32
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,920
You... you're home already?

33
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,750
You're home so early.

34
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:33,070
I'm in a meeting outside.

35
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,270
What's the matter?

36
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:35,200
Nothing.

37
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,590
I just met with a client.

38
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:40,400
I was just wondering if you're coming home for dinner tonight.

39
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,710
I'll be home for dinner.

40
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:43,750
Um, when you get home,

41
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:44,870
take a rest first.

42
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:45,960
I'll be home soon

43
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,310
and cook for you, okay?

44
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:48,579
Let me cook.

45
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:50,980
I'll do it. Just wait for me.

46
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,370
Alright, I'll hang up now.

47
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:04,000
I'm home.

48
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:22,190
Why aren't the lights on?

49
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:23,680
What's wrong?

50
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,600
Braised eggplant?

51
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:41,190
I love braised eggplant.

52
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:49,070
Why didn't your division chief keep you today

53
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:50,270
for social engagements?

54
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,000
Today we...

55
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:55,460
had a meeting. There's a working meal.

56
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:58,040
You're home quite early today,

57
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,130
and you've even made dinner.

58
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:05,130
I saw you today.

59
00:06:07,630 --> 00:06:08,510
Where?

60
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:12,590
You were eating ice cream.

61
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:34,150
That's the waitress from the service

62
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:35,570
department of our office.

63
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,600
She's from our hometown.

64
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:44,120
Her dad used to work for my dad.

65
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,909
Later, she came to Jingbei

66
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,120
and couldn't find a job.

67
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,360
Her dad asked my dad to help,

68
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,500
and I got her a position at our unit.

69
00:06:54,870 --> 00:06:55,950
She's a contract worker.

70
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:57,220
No need to explain.

71
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,870
Just do what you think is right.

72
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:13,260
Qiu Hua.

73
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:16,750
Is there...

74
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,940
nothing else you want to say?

75
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:28,540
What do you want to hear?

76
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,680
Aren't you going to ask anything?

77
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,650
I've seen it all, haven't I?

78
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:45,570
Actually, I feel responsible

79
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,560
for where we are today.

80
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,310
On our wedding day, I went to court.

81
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,040
I didn't go back to your hometown for the wedding banquet,

82
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:06,160
and I still haven't gone on a honeymoon with you.

83
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:10,050
When I got fired, you didn't know.

84
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,270
Your dad introduced me to business,

85
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,490
and I chose to refuse.

86
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:19,920
In our relationship,

87
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,400
it's always been you taking care of me.

88
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:26,800
It's me who keeps disappointing your expectations.

89
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,440
It's all my fault.

90
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:39,710
I just want to live a good life with you,

91
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:43,400
to have a child,

92
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,860
and have grandchildren when we're old.

93
00:09:02,790 --> 00:09:04,130
But I've realized

94
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,230
we're not on the same path.

95
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,120
I can't keep up with you,

96
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:15,770
and you can't slow down.

97
00:09:19,990 --> 00:09:20,470
I...

98
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:23,050
really don't know

99
00:09:23,940 --> 00:09:25,170
what to do anymore.

100
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,280
Let's end this matter here.

101
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,200
Don't worry about me.

102
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,200
Just take care of yourself.

103
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:55,510
I want to remind you of one thing:

104
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,070
Do what's right for you.

105
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:03,480
Don't bring trouble

106
00:10:04,730 --> 00:10:06,380
to yourself or your dad.

107
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,320
Morning.

108
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:19,150
Morning.

109
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,080
Yingzi,

110
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,030
there's a package for you on the table.

111
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:23,150
It's quite heavy.

112
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:25,260
I couldn't make out who the sender is.

113
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:26,960
What on earth is this?

114
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:30,390
I don't remember ordering anything.

115
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:38,710
It's quite big too.

116
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:41,320
Come here and give me a hand.

117
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,510
Pull that out a bit.

118
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:43,850
Okay.

119
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:50,880
[Maintain Integrity and Uphold Justice]

120
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,630
This signature...

121
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:57,200
By Bingwen. Who's Bingwen?

122
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,100
My daddy.

123
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,480
Uncle?

124
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,440
Why did he send you this?

125
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:05,230
Could it be to urge you

126
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,320
to stick to your principles and be a good person?

127
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,630
Yes, that's the idea.

128
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,120
I was bragging to him before

129
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,330
about us moving to the 17th floor.

130
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,480
He said he would send me a big gift.

131
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,750
And here it is.

132
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:18,160
The handwriting is decent.

133
00:11:18,270 --> 00:11:19,240
Quite decent.

134
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:20,960
Then let's find a place to hang it.

135
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,920
Yeah, I want to find a place to hang it.

136
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,240
I'd love to hang it on the 17th floor.

137
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,630
The view from there is so relaxing.

138
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,320
You think we should hang it here?

139
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:30,840
Where should we hang it here?

140
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,080
On my forehead?

141
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:33,720
Forget it.

142
00:11:34,390 --> 00:11:37,360
The Liangcheng Law Firm's fate is still uncertain.

143
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:39,760
If we step on their heads now,

144
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,940
who knows what might happen?

145
00:11:42,150 --> 00:11:43,670
I know that too.

146
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:45,080
But I just can't let it go.

147
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:47,080
To be honest,

148
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,270
if we could really rent that 17th floor,

149
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:50,080
I'm telling you,

150
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:51,990
with that location,

151
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:53,640
we'd have more clients than we do now.

152
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:56,200
That 17th floor

153
00:11:57,270 --> 00:12:00,150
is the money tree in my mind.

154
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,510
Our firm already has a money tree now.

155
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:03,150
Where is it?

156
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:04,480
Tell me where it is.

157
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,320
Apart from these little plants,

158
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,120
where is the tree?

159
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:08,040
Xia Shu.

160
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,480
Xia Shu is our firm's money tree.

161
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,080
Look how much Xia Shu

162
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,960
has earned for our firm.

163
00:12:13,980 --> 00:12:15,500
That's all Xia Shu's performance.

164
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,120
Now look at us,

165
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,220
we're major shareholders.

166
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:19,360
but this small law firm

167
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,120
is now supported by Xia Shu.

168
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:22,580
What's that saying again?

169
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,750
We should give young people opportunities.

170
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:26,790
Xia Shu...

171
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:28,260
We've got a case!

172
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,660
Look, the young one came.

173
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:30,670
What kind of case is it?

174
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,320
Our firm has a new case.

175
00:12:32,550 --> 00:12:33,370
A new case?

176
00:12:35,510 --> 00:12:36,120
Here.

177
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,000
You take a look first.

178
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,720
I'm so thirsty.

179
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,750
I'm going to get some water.

180
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,160
Drink plenty.

181
00:12:40,390 --> 00:12:42,440
Our money tree must not get thirsty.

182
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:46,030
What kind of case is this?

183
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:48,670
This was introduced by Zhang Lan.

184
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:50,240
She has a close friend named Li Yuan

185
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,440
who

186
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:54,270
wants to fight with her mother-in-law for the guardianship of her husband.

187
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:55,440
The daughter-in-law

188
00:12:55,790 --> 00:12:58,670
wants to fight with the mother-in-law for the guardianship of her son?

189
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,640
Okay, have you made an appointment?

190
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:02,390
Yes, the client should be here soon.

191
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:04,550
Ms. Li,

192
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:07,000
although our firm has been established for less than a year,

193
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,730
we have already taken on many big cases.

194
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,200
Ms. Luo, Ms. Qiu,

195
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,270
Ms. Li has arrived.

196
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:15,840
These two are the founding partners of our firm.

197
00:13:15,860 --> 00:13:17,490
This is Ms. Luo, and this is Ms. Qiu.

198
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,550
Hello.

199
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:20,640
Hello.

200
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,080
Ms. Li,

201
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,360
let's sit inside.

202
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,670
I understand your situation

203
00:13:26,670 --> 00:13:28,510
roughly from what Zhang Lan told me,

204
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,480
but could you please

205
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:33,310
explain the details to us?

206
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:38,100
[Defendant Li Yuan]

207
00:13:33,350 --> 00:13:33,990
Thank you.

208
00:13:36,810 --> 00:13:39,330
My case is a bit complicated.

209
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:42,550
It's related to family and marriage.

210
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:44,670
Ms. Li,

211
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,080
as you can see,

212
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,510
the lawyers in our firm

213
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,630
are all women.

214
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:51,240
So we'll understand whatever you say.

215
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,680
You can speak freely.

216
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:55,670
We will also protect your privacy.

217
00:13:57,080 --> 00:14:00,510
If you have any concerns,

218
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,560
we can proceed without taking notes.

219
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:04,580
Thank you.

220
00:14:07,030 --> 00:14:08,320
My husband's name is Yuan Gang.

221
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:12,360
He had an accident during a dive,

222
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:14,380
and now he's brain-dead.

223
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:20,720
From when we first met to when we started dating,

224
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,390
and then got married,

225
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,120
our relationship has always been good.

226
00:14:26,140 --> 00:14:28,210
Sometimes I feel we're quite similar.

227
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:28,760
Really.

228
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,670
So we decided

229
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:31,650
not to have children

230
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:33,390
and just

231
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:36,000
live our own life, just the two of us.

232
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:39,080
We both really love extreme sports,

233
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:41,350
especially technical diving.

234
00:14:42,670 --> 00:14:44,080
We've been to

235
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,320
Palau, Manado, Anilao.

236
00:14:45,630 --> 00:14:46,630
We even planned that,

237
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:47,870
if we had the chance,

238
00:14:47,870 --> 00:14:49,510
we'd try cave diving in the future.

239
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:51,960
Yuan Gang and I aren't just a couple.

240
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:55,360
We're also dive buddies who trust each other completely.

241
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,240
Technical diving,

242
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,750
after all, is an extreme sport,

243
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,640
and it's full of danger.

244
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,440
When you're underwater,

245
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:04,080
even a small incident

246
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,280
can cause panic,

247
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:07,700
and panic usually leads to death.

248
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:09,840
Underwater,

249
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:12,110
we put each other's lives

250
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,630
completely in each other's hands.

251
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:17,150
This trip to the Philippines

252
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:20,390
was supposed to be a regular vacation.

253
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:22,320
But the night before I left,

254
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,430
the company suddenly called with something urgent,

255
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,630
so I let Yuan Gang go ahead first.

256
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:28,630
During those two days while waiting for me,

257
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:31,920
he had an accident.

258
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:35,080
This time, a group of five people went down together.

259
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,630
Then during the ascent,

260
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:39,120
they encountered turbulent currents

261
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:41,920
which scattered them apart.

262
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,910
By the time they found Yuan Gang,

263
00:15:45,910 --> 00:15:47,250
he was already unconscious.

264
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,030
At that time, I

265
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:53,670
I... I...

266
00:15:53,670 --> 00:15:55,030
immediately

267
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:56,750
rushed to the hospital,

268
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,080
and the doctor told me

269
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,270
he was brain dead

270
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:00,190
and wouldn't wake up.

271
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,560
It's been six months since it happened.

272
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,320
Is he in a hospital abroad now?

273
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:11,500
We treated him abroad for a while,

274
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,080
but soon the foreign doctors

275
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,200
gave up,

276
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:15,860
saying he wouldn't recover.

277
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,150
Their views on life and death

278
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:18,570
are different from ours.

279
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:21,910
They think pointless treatments

280
00:16:21,910 --> 00:16:23,360
are meaningless.

281
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,760
They asked me to sign and give up,

282
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,270
but I couldn't accept it.

283
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,670
I had to bring Yuan Gang back.

284
00:16:29,670 --> 00:16:31,610
I went through a lot of trouble to bring Yuan Gang back.

285
00:16:32,490 --> 00:16:34,380
Now he's lying in our hospital.

286
00:16:35,730 --> 00:16:36,380
So,

287
00:16:36,910 --> 00:16:37,910
how did the doctors here

288
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,650
diagnose him?

289
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,840
What did they say?

290
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:43,800
Take a look at this.

291
00:16:44,790 --> 00:16:47,000
The diagnosis from the doctors here is the same as the ones abroad.

292
00:17:08,310 --> 00:17:10,460
Ms. Li, you came here because...

293
00:17:11,270 --> 00:17:12,829
I've been sued by Yuan Gang's mother.

294
00:17:14,069 --> 00:17:16,200
She's trying to take guardianship of Yuan Gang.

295
00:17:16,290 --> 00:17:18,180
She's suing you now

296
00:17:18,369 --> 00:17:20,440
to revoke your guardianship.

297
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:22,520
Why?

298
00:17:23,030 --> 00:17:24,310
Probably because

299
00:17:24,589 --> 00:17:26,220
I'm discussing with the doctors

300
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,890
about stopping Yuan Gang's treatment.

301
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,620
He's never going to wake up.

302
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:50,540
He's only being kept alive by a respirator now,

303
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,180
allowing his body to remain in this world.

304
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,720
We've been together for 12 years,

305
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:58,110
five years of a relationship

306
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:00,640
and seven years of marriage.

307
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,590
I know him too well.

308
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:05,580
I know this isn't what he would want.

309
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,160
He wouldn't want to

310
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,230
live in this world like this.

311
00:18:10,370 --> 00:18:13,360
The doctors are now advising me to let go,

312
00:18:16,870 --> 00:18:17,840
and I've agreed.

313
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:19,730
But my mother-in-law doesn't agree.

314
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:22,790
So she's suing me now,

315
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:24,620
hoping to regain Yuan Gang's guardianship.

316
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:26,160
She wants Yuan Gang to stay

317
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,160
in this world just like he is now.

318
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:34,920
I'm going to the restroom.

319
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:36,050
Please continue.

320
00:18:41,260 --> 00:18:42,260
Ms. Luo...

321
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:43,900
It's alright.

322
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:47,720
Well, Ms. Luo's family previously

323
00:18:48,190 --> 00:18:51,400
experienced a similar situation.

324
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:53,400
So she might...

325
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:06,150
Doctor,

326
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:09,690
is there

327
00:19:11,990 --> 00:19:13,950
any possibility to save my mother?

328
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,940
As I mentioned earlier,

329
00:19:18,510 --> 00:19:19,940
if you insist,

330
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:21,590
we will do our utmost

331
00:19:21,590 --> 00:19:22,940
to provide treatment for your mother.

332
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,830
Given her current condition,

333
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,730
a tracheostomy is necessary,

334
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:28,710
but it may not be effective.

335
00:19:29,510 --> 00:19:30,400
This decision

336
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:32,910
requires careful consideration from both of you.

337
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:23,520
I love him.

338
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,310
I know he wouldn't want to

339
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:28,230
live like this.

340
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:30,330
But it's only been half a year, right?

341
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:31,640
His brain waves

342
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,480
have long since flatlined.

343
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,940
There's no activity at all.

344
00:20:36,270 --> 00:20:38,350
From a modern medical perspective,

345
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,170
he died six months ago.

346
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,070
So, how many children does his mother have?

347
00:20:44,270 --> 00:20:45,510
Yuan Gang is her only child.

348
00:20:46,790 --> 00:20:47,920
Then I understand why

349
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,550
his mother doesn't agree.

350
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:52,500
Actually, I understand why my mother-in-law is doing this.

351
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,810
Yuan Gang's father passed away early.

352
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,610
Now Yuan Gang is about to go too.

353
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,750
I can fully understand

354
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:03,810
her feelings of losing her son.

355
00:21:04,270 --> 00:21:05,670
But no matter what,

356
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,400
I can't let Yuan Gang

357
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,440
continue living like this.

358
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:11,830
Is it possible to wait a bit longer,

359
00:21:11,830 --> 00:21:14,180
like a year or two?

360
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,110
You don't know Yuan Gang.

361
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:16,880
You don't know

362
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:17,920
how vain he is.

363
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:20,480
He cares a lot about his appearance.

364
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,680
He's been working out for years

365
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:25,900
just to maintain his muscles.

366
00:21:26,030 --> 00:21:28,510
He's been on a light diet for years, very disciplined.

367
00:21:29,510 --> 00:21:30,500
It's only been half a year,

368
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:33,270
but his body has already changed.

369
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:35,400
The doctor told me

370
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,110
that if another year passes,

371
00:21:38,510 --> 00:21:41,000
his body will change completely.

372
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,000
He'll turn from a man

373
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:48,680
into a corpse with loose skin, a bloated belly,

374
00:21:49,380 --> 00:21:51,380
and thin legs.

375
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,480
We made a promise to each other

376
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:57,550
that if one day we encounter this situation,

377
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:59,270
one of us must take responsibility for the other.

378
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:01,310
I can't watch the person I love

379
00:22:01,310 --> 00:22:02,440
become like this.

380
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:05,090
I believe Yuan Gang wouldn't want this either.

381
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,670
Ms. Li, is money involved with you

382
00:22:08,910 --> 00:22:10,300
and your mother-in-law?

383
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:13,020
I've already given up my inheritance rights to Yuan Gang's property.

384
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,180
I told my mother-in-law

385
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:16,470
that I would take care of her in her old age.

386
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:18,640
But no matter what I promise,

387
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:19,750
she won't accept it.

388
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,230
She only wants Yuan Gang to live,

389
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:23,820
even without dignity,

390
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:25,680
even living like he is now.

391
00:22:29,430 --> 00:22:31,250
Actually, I'd like to ask you all,

392
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:33,940
as we're all women,

393
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:37,780
do you agree

394
00:22:39,020 --> 00:22:41,560
with how I'm handling this situation with Yuan Gang?

395
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:54,970
[Yinghua Law Firm]

396
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:56,850
Ms. Li,

397
00:22:57,290 --> 00:22:59,300
please review this agreement carefully when you go back.

398
00:22:59,550 --> 00:23:01,510
If there's no problem, just sign it

399
00:23:01,650 --> 00:23:03,440
and send us a copy.

400
00:23:03,810 --> 00:23:05,570
Alright, no need to see me out.

401
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:06,580
Goodbye.

402
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:11,920
Ms. Li has left.

403
00:23:20,180 --> 00:23:21,450
Don't you think

404
00:23:22,210 --> 00:23:24,660
she's making this decision a bit too hastily?

405
00:23:25,750 --> 00:23:28,120
After all, it's only been half a year since Yuan Gang was unconscious.

406
00:23:29,630 --> 00:23:30,870
I think anyone who's

407
00:23:30,890 --> 00:23:32,240
been through something similar

408
00:23:33,580 --> 00:23:34,870
would understand.

409
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:37,090
The living ones bear the heaviest burden

410
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,860
when sending off the one they love most.

411
00:23:40,790 --> 00:23:42,780
Does she truly love Yuan Gang?

412
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,260
I believe she does.

413
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:48,200
But let's be honest,

414
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,270
this has nothing to do

415
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:51,480
with love anymore.

416
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:54,230
Yuan Gang is already brain-dead.

417
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:56,720
I think the best choice for her

418
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,350
is to let him go.

419
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:01,440
This way, it's better for both the people around him

420
00:24:02,070 --> 00:24:03,160
and for

421
00:24:03,830 --> 00:24:04,440
himself.

422
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,270
It's almost four o'clock.

423
00:24:10,270 --> 00:24:11,510
Today has been a bit heavy.

424
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,550
Let's call it a day

425
00:24:12,750 --> 00:24:13,530
and go home.

426
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:17,910
Perfect, I have a date.

427
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,370
Like no one else has a date.

428
00:24:20,780 --> 00:24:21,480
I don't.

429
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:28,150
Well, I won't be able to give you a ride today.

430
00:24:28,170 --> 00:24:29,580
Chen Shuo asked me to dinner.

431
00:24:30,710 --> 00:24:32,070
You both go on your dates.

432
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:33,150
I'll stay here and work.

433
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,240
I'm off.

434
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,550
Mr. Chen, you're finally here.

435
00:24:42,550 --> 00:24:43,220
Hello, Lisa.

436
00:24:43,750 --> 00:24:44,550
Please, come in.

437
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,030
Lisa?

438
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:49,960
Looks like you're a regular here.

439
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:50,930
Everyone knows you.

440
00:24:51,350 --> 00:24:52,300
How could I not be?

441
00:24:52,350 --> 00:24:53,270
You have no idea

442
00:24:53,270 --> 00:24:54,830
how many times I've saved you a seat here,

443
00:24:54,830 --> 00:24:56,060
and ended up alone every time.

444
00:24:56,550 --> 00:24:58,650
I've paid nearly 5,000 yuan in deposits alone.

445
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,370
Why are you talking about money?

446
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:01,790
Are you expecting me to reimburse you?

447
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:03,230
No way.

448
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:04,160
No need.

449
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:06,750
How is it?

450
00:25:07,510 --> 00:25:08,450
It looks great.

451
00:25:09,270 --> 00:25:10,040
So spacious.

452
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:13,650
Mr. Chen,

453
00:25:13,860 --> 00:25:14,420
here's the menu.

454
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:16,200
Okay, one more for the lady.

455
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:17,310
Okay, thank you.

456
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,000
Seize the opportunity.

457
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:20,410
You can really let me splurge today.

458
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:22,750
Alright, fancy menu.

459
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,510
This took some thought.

460
00:25:26,870 --> 00:25:28,300
What should I order?

461
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:34,800
Two red cubilose and two sea cucumbers with millet.

462
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:35,640
Okay.

463
00:25:37,230 --> 00:25:38,010
No, no, no.

464
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:40,110
I was just messing with him.

465
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,160
We don't want any of these.

466
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:44,900
Um, do you have any home-style dishes?

467
00:25:45,890 --> 00:25:47,000
I'm sorry, miss.

468
00:25:47,070 --> 00:25:48,240
We don't have home-style dishes.

469
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:49,440
She's just kidding with you.

470
00:25:50,110 --> 00:25:50,960
I'm not.

471
00:25:51,270 --> 00:25:52,180
It's okay. Let me order.

472
00:25:52,450 --> 00:25:53,310
Two red cubilose,

473
00:25:54,550 --> 00:25:55,320
fish maw and yellow croaker soup,

474
00:25:56,090 --> 00:25:57,040
braised Hangzhou cabbage,

475
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:58,960
and crab roe tofu.

476
00:25:58,960 --> 00:25:59,430
Alright.

477
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:00,870
Thank you.

478
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:02,430
Thank you, Lisa.

479
00:26:04,560 --> 00:26:05,430
What do you mean?

480
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:07,310
We're not even married yet.

481
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:08,320
You're saving me money?

482
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:09,880
That's not like you.

483
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:11,270
Then you...

484
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:13,030
Do you still want it or not?

485
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:14,860
Yes, yes, yes.

486
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:37,190
A toast to what?

487
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,480
How would I know?

488
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:41,390
Just having a drink.

489
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:45,360
To the two-year anniversary of our car crash.

490
00:26:47,110 --> 00:26:48,270
To me meeting you.

491
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:50,640
To our beautiful future life together.

492
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:02,640
Can we discuss something?

493
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:05,160
We're together now.

494
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:06,820
Let's live together.

495
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:11,510
Why? Are you nervous?

496
00:27:12,350 --> 00:27:13,790
It's okay if you don't want to live at my place.

497
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:16,020
We can go to your old house.

498
00:27:16,750 --> 00:27:17,880
No, no, no, don't frown.

499
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:18,940
Listen to me,

500
00:27:19,030 --> 00:27:20,760
when the bank took your house before,

501
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,400
leaving you homeless, it was quite pitiful,

502
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,820
but that wasn't my intention at all.

503
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,590
I spent 6 million more than the market price

504
00:27:25,590 --> 00:27:26,920
to buy it back. Why?

505
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:29,000
Just so you'd have a home.

506
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,640
To give the house back to you.

507
00:27:31,110 --> 00:27:31,910
Are you touched?

508
00:27:32,390 --> 00:27:33,120
Alright.

509
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:35,510
So I'll move into that house,

510
00:27:36,270 --> 00:27:37,640
and every day

511
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:38,910
I'll see Liu Ming's phantom.

512
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:41,430
Three of us living happily together.

513
00:27:42,290 --> 00:27:43,180
Such a mood killer.

514
00:27:43,210 --> 00:27:44,650
Why bring him up?

515
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:46,160
I've told you before,

516
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:47,620
don't mention that house to me again.

517
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,070
I will never,

518
00:27:49,070 --> 00:27:50,420
ever set foot in that house again.

519
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:52,880
Chen Shuo,

520
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,320
are you really that stupid?

521
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,680
Can't you just sell that house

522
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:57,990
and buy a new one?

523
00:27:58,360 --> 00:27:59,270
And put it in your name?

524
00:27:59,590 --> 00:28:00,880
Now I'm truly touched.

525
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:03,050
Alright then, I'll sell it and buy you a new one.

526
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,510
But what you just said...

527
00:28:09,030 --> 00:28:10,070
Xue said that too.

528
00:28:10,190 --> 00:28:10,950
What did he say?

529
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:13,160
Three people living in a

530
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,270
familiar space,

531
00:28:14,270 --> 00:28:15,630
and I can't avoid

532
00:28:15,650 --> 00:28:16,960
seeing a man every day.

533
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:19,110
See?

534
00:28:19,110 --> 00:28:20,670
Xue's so considerate and on point when he speaks.

535
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:23,690
You should learn from him, okay?

536
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:24,360
Alright.

537
00:28:25,790 --> 00:28:27,310
I'm going to the restroom.

538
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:29,640
Looks like you really

539
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,720
know this place well.

540
00:28:30,740 --> 00:28:32,380
This is what we call being in sync, okay?

541
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,480
Anyway, I don't know Lisa.

542
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:18,720
How did it turn into a candlelit dinner

543
00:29:18,750 --> 00:29:20,270
when I come back?

544
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:22,510
Just now we had fish maw and red cubilose.

545
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:24,140
It's too extravagant, lacking romance.

546
00:29:27,130 --> 00:29:28,130
A piece of cake,

547
00:29:29,270 --> 00:29:30,070
a few roses,

548
00:29:30,070 --> 00:29:31,400
and a couple candles make it romantic?

549
00:29:31,510 --> 00:29:32,320
Not bad, right?

550
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:36,070
Don't tell me

551
00:29:36,070 --> 00:29:36,920
there's something

552
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:38,750
hidden in this cake.

553
00:29:39,510 --> 00:29:41,030
I don't want to see anything.

554
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:42,420
There's a ring inside.

555
00:29:43,510 --> 00:29:44,120
Really?

556
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:50,940
You're too violent.

557
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:54,990
Good thing there's nothing in it,

558
00:29:55,740 --> 00:29:57,020
otherwise it would be so tacky.

559
00:29:58,810 --> 00:29:59,720
It tastes pretty good though.

560
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:04,240
If there really was something in here,

561
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:06,160
you'd think it's really tacky and stupid, right?

562
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:08,190
Yeah, extremely stupid.

563
00:30:08,860 --> 00:30:10,690
Uncreative and very tacky.

564
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:12,810
It doesn't match your image

565
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:15,380
of being smart and tasteful.

566
00:30:16,030 --> 00:30:16,730
Am I tasteful?

567
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:17,920
Yeah.

568
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:19,350
You've become much more tasteful

569
00:30:19,350 --> 00:30:20,160
since you met me.

570
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,260
