848
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:17,710
Chen Shuo is not supposed to be such a person.

849
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,920
Could there be something behind it?

850
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:22,510
I don't know what his problem is

851
00:41:22,510 --> 00:41:23,440
or what he's hiding.

852
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:24,480
He could just tell me.

853
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:26,160
I've asked him many times, but he just wouldn't tell me why.

854
00:41:26,230 --> 00:41:28,190
I told him I never interfered with his cases,

855
00:41:28,190 --> 00:41:29,510
so why is he interfering with mine?

856
00:41:29,630 --> 00:41:31,510
Does this mean for every case I represent in the future,

857
00:41:31,510 --> 00:41:32,510
if he doesn't approve,

858
00:41:32,510 --> 00:41:33,660
I can't take it?

859
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:36,440
How am I supposed to do my job?

860
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:38,570
You two have come a long way to be together.

861
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:41,800
Don't let these work issues get in the way

862
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:42,710
of your relationship.

863
00:41:42,710 --> 00:41:43,670
It's not worth it.

864
00:41:43,670 --> 00:41:44,740
So what do you think I should do?

865
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,340
Should I just agree with him

866
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:47,230
and not take the case?

867
00:41:48,030 --> 00:41:49,210
But that's not me.

868
00:41:49,470 --> 00:41:50,630
Why should I back down?

869
00:41:51,510 --> 00:41:52,170
Yingzi,

870
00:41:53,510 --> 00:41:55,360
let's put Chen Shuo aside.

871
00:41:55,740 --> 00:41:57,110
I just want to ask you,

872
00:41:57,110 --> 00:41:58,980
why do you insist on taking this case?

873
00:41:59,420 --> 00:42:01,060
Is it because of your mom?

874
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:06,790
That's part of it,

875
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:08,200
but not the whole reason.

876
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:11,960
Back then, the doctor told my dad and me

877
00:42:12,380 --> 00:42:13,780
to make the decision

878
00:42:14,050 --> 00:42:15,970
whether to end my mom's treatment.

879
00:42:16,290 --> 00:42:17,340
But in the end,

880
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:18,760
it was my dad who made the decision.

881
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:19,800
He was the one who signed.

882
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:22,110
So I've always felt uneasy

883
00:42:22,110 --> 00:42:23,070
about this.

884
00:42:23,300 --> 00:42:24,340
I think

885
00:42:24,560 --> 00:42:26,330
you might be letting your emotions

886
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:27,870
influence you too much in this case.

887
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:30,150
There is indeed an emotional factor,

888
00:42:30,510 --> 00:42:31,360
but

889
00:42:33,190 --> 00:42:34,690
that's another story, right?

890
00:42:35,110 --> 00:42:36,000
Like I said,

891
00:42:36,060 --> 00:42:38,060
am I not a professional lawyer?

892
00:42:38,190 --> 00:42:39,530
No matter how much

893
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:41,070
my personal factors are involved,

894
00:42:41,070 --> 00:42:42,710
I wouldn't let emotions cloud my judgment

895
00:42:42,710 --> 00:42:43,820
in taking this case.

896
00:42:46,420 --> 00:42:47,520
Forget it.

897
00:42:48,190 --> 00:42:49,310
To be honest,

898
00:42:50,590 --> 00:42:51,710
leaving Chen Shuo out of this,

899
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:55,550
I don't quite agree with how Li Yuan

900
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,460
is handling this situation.

901
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,000
After all, her husband's been

902
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,320
in a coma for only half a year,

903
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:01,550
and she's giving up on his treatment

904
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:02,530
and let him go.

905
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,400
But what if he just doesn't wake up?
